| Field       | Value              |
| ----------- | ------------------ |
| Name        | `web-rds-sg`       |
| Description | EC2 and RDS access |
| VPC         | `demo-vpc`         |

---

# STEP 9 — Configure Inbound Rules

Add these rules:

| Type         | Port | Source       |
| ------------ | ---- | ------------ |
| SSH          | 22   | My IP        |
| HTTP         | 80   | `0.0.0.0/0`  |
| HTTPS        | 443  | `0.0.0.0/0`  |
| MySQL/Aurora | 3306 | `web-rds-sg` |

IMPORTANT:

For MySQL source:

* Select **Custom**
* Choose SAME security group (`web-rds-sg`)

This allows:

* EC2 ↔ RDS communication inside SG

Create security group.

