# FINAL SECURITY GROUP CONFIGURATION

## web-rds-sg

### Inbound Rules

| Type  | Port | Source       |
| ----- | ---- | ------------ |
| SSH   | 22   | My IP        |
| HTTP  | 80   | `0.0.0.0/0`  |
| HTTPS | 443  | `0.0.0.0/0`  |
| MySQL | 3306 | `web-rds-sg` |

---

# IMPORTANT CONCEPT

Why use same SG as source?

```text
Source = web-rds-sg
```

means:

> Any resource using this SG can communicate on port 3306.

So:

* EC2 can connect to RDS
* RDS remains private
* MySQL not exposed publicly

---

# Common Errors and Fixes

## ERROR: Can't connect to MySQL

Check:

* RDS status = Available
* Same VPC used
* Same SG attached
* Port 3306 rule exists
* Correct endpoint
* Correct password

---

## ERROR: Apache page not loading

Check:

```bash
sudo systemctl status apache2
```

Also verify:

* EC2 has public IP
* HTTP port 80 open

---

## ERROR: PHP code downloading instead of executing

Install PHP module:

```bash
sudo apt install libapache2-mod-php -y
```

Restart Apache:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

